qas.question: What acoustic element could be distorted by different audio settings in iPods prior to 2007?
Name four sound profiles that would result in bass distortion on pre-2007 iPods.

answers.text: R&B, Rock, Acoustic, and Bass Booster

qas.question: What specific problem caused the issue with bass distortion?
iPods released before what year had issues with distorted bass?
What EQ settings were known to have issues with bass distortion?

answers.text: R&B, Rock, Acoustic, and Bass Booster

context: For all iPods released in <a3_0>2006<a3_0/> and earlier, some equalizer (EQ) sound settings would distort the bass sound far too easily, even on undemanding songs. This would happen for EQ settings like <a1_0><a4_0>R&B, Rock, Acoustic, and <a0_0>Bass<a0_0/> Booster<a4_0/><a1_0/>, because the equalizer amplified the digital audio level beyond the software's limit, causing distortion (<a2_0>clipping<a2_0/>) on bass instruments.
